HEADWORD: Santonic
<hw>San*ton"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid (distinct from
santoninic acid) obtained from santonin as a white crystalline
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

